\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. S. nodulosa} Viv.,{\i  Fl. Cors.} 6 (1824) ({\i S. pauciflora} Salzm. ex DC., non Ucria). Perennial with rather slender, branched, woody stock and numerous slender flowering stems up to 30 cm; lower part of stem and leaves scabrid-puberulent. Lower leaves up to 30 × 5 mm, oblanceolate to narrowly spathulate; upper cauline leaves linear, distant. Inflorescence glabrous, (1)2- to 5-flowered; pedicels up to 7 cm, very slender. Calyx 18-20 mm, narrow, glabrous; teeth obtuse, more or less ciliate. Petals white, reddish beneath. Capsule c. 10 mm, ovoid; carpophore c. 12 mm, glabrous. Seeds c. 1 mm, black. 2n = 24. •{\i  Corse; Sardegna.} Co Sa.
