\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. S. spinescens} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1:} 299 (1809). Stock very woody, much-branched; flowering stems 10-30 cm, erect, bearing numerous, non-flowering, rigid branches below, forming a spiny, persistent cushion. Basal leaves spathulate; cauline leaves linear, stiff, often spinose; leaves and stems greyish-tomentose. Inflorescence-branches mostly 1-flowered. Calyx c. 20 mm, pubescent; teeth obtuse. Petals white, deeply bifid; coronal scales ovate. Capsule c. 1½ times as long as carpophore. 2n = 24. {\i • S.E. Greece}. Gr.
