\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 20. S. fruticosa} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 417 (1753). Robust perennial up to 50 cm, almost completely glabrous. Lower leaves obovate or narrowly spathulate, the upper lanceolate; all glabrous and shining above, ciliate. Inflorescence dense; flowers large, erect, on short peduncles. Calyx c. 25 mm, with patent glandular hairs; teeth acute. Petals pink or red, shallowly bifid; coronal scales obvious, acute, sometimes laciniate. Capsule c. 15 mm, ovoid, beaked, equalling or longer than carpophore. Seeds 1·5-2 mm. 2n = 24. {\i  • Mediterranean region} ({\i Sicilia to Karpathos}); {\i very local.} Cr Gr Si.
