\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. S. nutans} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 417 (1753). Stems 20-60(-100) cm, usually unbranched, and obviously pubescent below, rarely glabrous. Lower leaves up to 10 cm, oblong-spathulate, the upper linear-lanceolate. Flowers usually inclined, in a lax, secund panicle. Calyx 9-12 mm, glandular-pubescent, truncate at base; teeth lanceolate, acute. Petals variable in colour, usually whitish above, greenish or reddish beneath, deeply bifid with narrow, inrolled lobes; coronal scales lanceolate, acute. Capsule 7-13(-18) mm, 3-5 times as long as pubescent carpophore.{\i  Usually calcicole. Most of Europe except the extreme north and most of the islands.} Al Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs(N, B, C, W, E) Su.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Extremely variable in habit, hairiness, leaf-shape, colour and size of flowers, and size of capsule.
